00:56:57,713 --> 00:57:00,682
I'd double over in pain,
I'd be gasping for breath.

769
00:57:02,485 --> 00:57:04,646
Mmm. What else?

770
00:57:05,521 --> 00:57:06,818
I don't know.

771
00:57:06,989 --> 00:57:07,978
[Laughing]

772
00:57:08,257 --> 00:57:09,554
[Groans]

773
00:57:09,625 --> 00:57:10,751
[Moaning]

774
00:57:10,826 --> 00:57:11,884
Okay, now.

775
00:57:12,495 --> 00:57:15,362
You've got the doubling over
and gasping for air part right.

776
00:57:15,431 --> 00:57:19,162
But there's also that burning sensation
in your gut, the pounding in your head...

777
00:57:19,235 --> 00:57:20,827
the weak legs and teary eyes.

778
00:57:21,837 --> 00:57:24,863
Oh, notice the snot hanging out of your nose.

779
00:57:26,242 --> 00:57:29,211
There's a feeling that
you're never gonna breathe again, and then...

780
00:57:29,278 --> 00:57:31,337
your lungs fill with cool, fresh air.

781
00:57:31,847 --> 00:57:33,405
[Gasping]

782
00:57:36,619 --> 00:57:38,052
That's experience.

783
00:57:39,688 --> 00:57:40,746
[Groaning]

784
00:57:40,823 --> 00:57:42,950
Stop trying to manipulate me.

785
00:58:09,452 --> 00:58:11,647
Father, am I disturbing you?

786
00:58:12,021 --> 00:58:14,990
No. No, no, my son.

787
00:58:15,524 --> 00:58:20,052
I... I was just preparing the sacraments
for the evening prayer.

788
00:58:22,198 --> 00:58:25,065
I, uh, I've been expecting you.

789
00:58:26,402 --> 00:58:28,029
- You have?
- Yes.

790
00:58:29,738 --> 00:58:32,400
I am a priest, and part of my job...

791
00:58:32,475 --> 00:58:35,842
is to help those who need it.

792
00:58:38,647 --> 00:58:41,081
You wish to speak about Weldon and writing.

793
00:58:53,729 --> 00:58:55,060
So how do I reach him?

794
00:58:56,499 --> 00:58:58,228
Do you believe in fate?

795
00:59:01,270 --> 00:59:03,864
Uh, Father, I don't know.

796
00:59:04,240 --> 00:59:07,869
I do. I believe that each of us...

797
00:59:07,943 --> 00:59:10,707
are predestined to walk a path in life.

798
00:59:11,680 --> 00:59:14,205
Along this path we meet others...

799
00:59:14,550 --> 00:59:17,951
and through knowing them,
we change their lives.

800
00:59:20,256 --> 00:59:23,191
Okay, but what does that have to do
with Weldon and writing?

801
00:59:25,461 --> 00:59:28,294
There is an old story
about a bird who loved to fly.

802
00:59:29,265 --> 00:59:33,224
One day, while he was high up in the air...

803
00:59:33,869 --> 00:59:35,336
it began to rain...

804
00:59:35,871 --> 00:59:38,567
and its feathers became so heavy...

805
00:59:38,641 --> 00:59:42,600
that when it tried to land, it broke its wing.

806
00:59:44,246 --> 00:59:47,613
Time passed, and the bird became better.

807
00:59:48,317 --> 00:59:52,879
It wanted to fly,
but no matter how hard it tried...

808
00:59:53,088 --> 00:59:56,649
something inside stopped it
from leaving the ground.

809
00:59:57,693 --> 01:00:00,787
Day after day it tried, and day after day...

810
01:00:01,263 --> 01:00:03,561
its fear held it down.

811
01:00:04,333 --> 01:00:07,359
Then one day, a strong wind came...

812
01:00:07,670 --> 01:00:10,002
and lifted it high into the sky.

813
01:00:11,407 --> 01:00:16,276
It opened its wings
and it realized that it could fly.

814
01:00:16,345 --> 01:00:19,678
I know. Okay. I get it, I do.

815
01:00:19,748 --> 01:00:22,376
Weldon's the bird and he's afraid to fly, right?

816
01:00:23,586 --> 01:00:24,917
No, Jeremy.

817
01:00:25,454 --> 01:00:28,287
Weldon is the bird, and you are the wind.

818
01:00:30,626 --> 01:00:33,390
That is the path fate's chosen for you.

819
01:00:43,606 --> 01:00:45,369
[Birds chirping]

820
01:00:53,249 --> 01:00:54,716
[Door closing]

821
01:01:01,457 --> 01:01:02,549
Hi.

822
01:01:03,993 --> 01:01:05,483
Hello.

823
01:01:14,370 --> 01:01:17,305
Father Moretti tells me
you had a nice little chat today.

824
01:01:18,974 --> 01:01:21,636
Obviously I didn't punch you
in the stomach hard enough.

825
01:01:26,615 --> 01:01:28,344
I need to apologize for earlier.

826
01:01:30,252 --> 01:01:34,814
Look, I only went to speak with Father Moretti
because I didn't understand what hap...

827
01:01:37,426 --> 01:01:39,917
- This is my manuscript.
- I know.

828
01:01:40,929 --> 01:01:42,396
Where did you get this?

829
01:01:42,464 --> 01:01:45,956
I went to the hotel and told Gustavo
you wanted me to get it for you.

830
01:01:48,170 --> 01:01:50,229
You had no right to do that, Weldon.

831
01:01:51,907 --> 01:01:53,374
You've got talent, Jeremy.

832
01:01:57,413 --> 01:01:58,744
You're a good writer.

833
01:01:59,415 --> 01:02:01,576
The problem is, you don't trust your talent.

834
01:02:02,584 --> 01:02:06,076
You don't believe you can find that part of you
that has something to say.

835
01:02:09,458 --> 01:02:10,618
Well...

836
01:02:12,194 --> 01:02:16,255
- How do I know when I've found it?
- Believe me, there's no mistaking it.

837
01:02:17,933 --> 01:02:20,595
I know there's a lot of time and effort
put into those pages.

838
01:02:20,669 --> 01:02:22,694
Have enough faith in yourself to let them go.

839
01:02:23,772 --> 01:02:26,434
Take what you've learned from them
and start again.

840
01:02:57,072 --> 01:02:58,130
[Sighing]

841
01:03:07,950 --> 01:03:09,076
Ciao.

842
01:03:13,389 --> 01:03:15,380
[Speaking Italian]

843
01:03:16,993 --> 01:03:19,985
[Speaking Italian]

844
01:03:21,497 --> 01:03:23,465
I have absolutely no idea what you just said.

845
01:03:23,533 --> 01:03:24,898
But it sounds good.

846
01:03:25,168 --> 01:03:28,069
- Want some company?
- Sure. Come.

847
01:03:29,405 --> 01:03:31,168
With the horses, huh?

848
01:03:34,544 --> 01:03:35,704
[Clearing throat]

849
01:03:58,935 --> 01:04:02,962
Jesus, I'm gonna die.

850
01:04:05,942 --> 01:04:07,000
[Neighing]

851
01:04:07,577 --> 01:04:08,669
Phew.

852
01:04:08,744 --> 01:04:10,143
[Both laughing]

853
01:04:10,846 --> 01:04:13,110
When was the last time you were on a horse?

854
01:04:13,182 --> 01:04:15,241
Uh, let's see...

855
01:04:15,785 --> 01:04:19,312
the last time I was on a horse was, um...

856
01:04:19,388 --> 01:04:22,482
Oh, whoa. Uh, that would be never.

857
01:04:22,592 --> 01:04:24,856
- Never?
- Yes, never.

858
01:04:24,927 --> 01:04:28,556
- Why did you come?
- It's a new experience. I'm big on... Oh.

859
01:04:28,631 --> 01:04:30,496
[Chuckling] Big on new experiences lately.

860
01:04:33,936 --> 01:04:36,097
[Grunting]

861
01:04:37,707 --> 01:04:39,402
[Laughing]

862
01:04:47,583 --> 01:04:48,675
[Birds chirping]

863
01:04:48,751 --> 01:04:50,343
WELDON: So how is the writing going?

864
01:04:51,587 --> 01:04:52,918
[Sighing]

865
01:04:54,423 --> 01:04:57,290
Um, I don't know, actually.

866
01:04:58,594 --> 01:05:03,497
I'm really starting to question whether or not
I have what it takes.

867
01:05:04,133 --> 01:05:06,533
Ah, yes, self-doubt.

868
01:05:07,703 --> 01:05:09,967
It is a common thing with creative people.

869
01:05:11,140 --> 01:05:13,370
Do you find that a lot of creative people are...

870
01:05:14,410 --> 01:05:16,708
- Crazy?
- Yes, crazy.

871
01:05:16,779 --> 01:05:18,542
[Chuckling] Of course, they're crazy.

872
01:05:19,315 --> 01:05:21,749
There are thousands of writers and artists.

873
01:05:22,184 --> 01:05:25,642
For most of them,
their dreams will never come true.

874
01:05:26,555 --> 01:05:27,954
You have to be crazy.

875
01:05:30,226 --> 01:05:32,285
Well, thanks, Weldon, that's very encouraging.

876
01:05:33,462 --> 01:05:35,259
No, that's reality, Jeremy.

877
01:05:35,765 --> 01:05:37,960
Art is not something you choose to do.

878
01:05:38,801 --> 01:05:40,666
It's something that chooses you.

879
01:05:42,905 --> 01:05:44,839
Why did you wanna become a writer?

880
01:05:47,843 --> 01:05:52,041
- Because I think that I have...
- No, it's not something you think.

881
01:05:52,648 --> 01:05:54,047
It's something you know.

882
01:05:54,950 --> 01:05:56,645
Tell me when you know the answer.

883
01:05:57,320 --> 01:05:58,787
[Isabella speaking Italian]

884
01:05:58,854 --> 01:05:59,980
[Dog barking]

885
01:06:05,661 --> 01:06:08,027
It's amazing how much
she looks like her mother.

886
01:06:09,665 --> 01:06:12,600
Sometimes I'll walk into her room
and for a moment I'll think...

887
01:06:16,806 --> 01:06:17,966
[Speaking Italian]

888
01:06:19,775 --> 01:06:21,208
Describe her to me.

889
01:06:22,845 --> 01:06:25,712
- Come on, not this again.
- Just do it, will you?

890
01:06:27,950 --> 01:06:29,144
[Sighing]

891
01:06:38,394 --> 01:06:42,831
Sunlight frames her body
in a golden glow of honeyed light...

892
01:06:44,266 --> 01:06:47,633
while the wind dances gently
through the long strands of her hair.

893
01:06:50,373 --> 01:06:53,001
Her face is strong, proud...

894
01:06:54,844 --> 01:06:57,642
with eyes that don't easily
give away their secrets.

895
01:07:00,816 --> 01:07:02,681
It's a face that doesn't call out...

896
01:07:04,220 --> 01:07:05,482
but softly beckons.

897
01:07:10,860 --> 01:07:11,986
How was that?

898
01:07:15,264 --> 01:07:16,697
You tell me.

899
01:07:27,109 --> 01:07:28,303
By the way...

900
01:07:28,878 --> 01:07:31,312
how long have you been
in love with my daughter?

901
01:07:51,500 --> 01:07:53,092
[Headboard banging on wall]

902
01:07:53,169 --> 01:07:54,830
[Woman moaning]

903
01:08:03,145 --> 01:08:05,978
[Both speaking Italian]

904
01:08:13,322 --> 01:08:14,414
No.

905
01:08:18,561 --> 01:08:20,028
- Ciao, Weldon.
- Ciao.

906
01:08:23,566 --> 01:08:24,692
What?

907
01:08:27,036 --> 01:08:28,833
You two are the couple next door?

908
01:08:32,007 --> 01:08:33,531
Are you ready for the party?

909
01:08:35,911 --> 01:08:37,742
[Snickering] Yeah.

910
01:08:38,848 --> 01:08:40,816
[Accordion music playing]

911
01:08:40,883 --> 01:08:42,214
[People chattering]

912
01:09:28,063 --> 01:09:31,555
I wasn't stealing. I was accepting charity.

913
01:09:32,968 --> 01:09:35,960
GUSTAVO: Weldon, it's going to be
a late night.

914
01:09:36,405 --> 01:09:38,134
Why don't you all stay at the hotel?

915
01:09:42,511 --> 01:09:44,001
Half price, of course.

916
01:09:46,782 --> 01:09:48,010
Okay, free.

917
01:09:50,953 --> 01:09:52,818
[Accordion music playing]

918
01:10:34,029 --> 01:10:36,725
[Sway playing]

919
01:10:46,275 --> 01:10:50,006
When marimba rhythms start to play

920
01:10:50,079 --> 01:10:54,106
Dance with me, make me sway

921
01:10:54,450 --> 01:10:57,908
Like a lazy ocean hugs the shore

922
01:10:57,987 --> 01:11:01,821
Hold me close, sway me more

923
01:11:02,458 --> 01:11:05,950
Like a flower bendin' in the breeze

924
01:11:06,028 --> 01:11:10,431
Bend with me, sway with ease

925
01:11:10,499 --> 01:11:13,900
When we dance, you have a way with me

926
01:11:13,969 --> 01:11:17,837
Stay with me, sway with me

927
01:11:18,507 --> 01:11:22,068
Other dancers may be on the floor

928
01:11:22,544 --> 01:11:26,378
Dear, but my eyes will see only you

929
01:11:26,448 --> 01:11:30,248
Only you have the magic technique

930
01:11:30,319 --> 01:11:34,346
When we sway, I grow weak

931
01:11:34,423 --> 01:11:38,086
I can hear the sound of violins

932
01:11:38,160 --> 01:11:42,563
Long before it begins

933
01:11:42,631 --> 01:11:46,123
Make me thrill as only you know how

934
01:11:46,201 --> 01:11:50,934
Sway me smooth, sway me now

935
01:11:58,981 --> 01:12:00,471
[Birds chirping]

936
01:12:01,617 --> 01:12:02,811
[Groaning]

937
01:12:18,300 --> 01:12:20,268
You were gone when I woke up this morning.

938
01:12:23,072 --> 01:12:24,596
You had a dream.

939
01:12:26,975 --> 01:12:29,205
It's funny 'cause it felt pretty real to me.

940
01:12:32,014 --> 01:12:34,915
Yes, but last night was last night.

941
01:12:37,786 --> 01:12:39,413
What exactly does that mean?

942
01:12:41,056 --> 01:12:43,524
It means I wanted to see how I felt with you.

943
01:12:45,928 --> 01:12:47,327
And how did you feel?

944
01:12:49,131 --> 01:12:50,325
Jeremy...

945
01:12:51,867 --> 01:12:53,835
we live in different worlds, uh?

946
01:12:56,872 --> 01:12:59,568
There's no reason
why you couldn't come and live in my world.

947
01:13:01,677 --> 01:13:03,770
Do I look like I belong in London?

948
01:13:04,947 --> 01:13:08,815
My life is here with my family and my horses.

949
01:13:08,884 --> 01:13:10,181
[Sighing]

950
01:13:10,452 --> 01:13:12,784
Isabella, I don't wanna just let this slip away.

951
01:13:14,890 --> 01:13:16,118
I know.

952
01:13:19,962 --> 01:13:21,793
I'm sorry, I...

953
01:13:23,932 --> 01:13:26,093
I just wanted to share something with you.

954
01:13:50,359 --> 01:13:52,520
JEREMY: You wanna know
what my problem really is?

955
01:13:53,395 --> 01:13:54,419
I'm afraid.

956
01:13:56,966 --> 01:13:57,955
WELDON: Of what?

957
01:13:59,969 --> 01:14:00,958
Of life.

958
01:14:02,004 --> 01:14:04,336
Of love. Of everything.

959
01:14:07,076 --> 01:14:08,668
I want my own villa, Weldon.

960
01:14:10,146 --> 01:14:12,046
I wanna grow grapes and write great novels.

961
01:14:12,114 --> 01:14:13,672
[Both chuckling]

962
01:14:14,383 --> 01:14:15,941
So what's stopping you?

963
01:14:18,454 --> 01:14:19,478
Fear.

964
01:14:20,556 --> 01:14:23,821
Fear... I mean, I've built this whole life
for myself in London.

965
01:14:23,893 --> 01:14:26,020
I don't think I can just change.

966
01:14:28,831 --> 01:14:30,059
Well, Jeremy...

967
01:14:31,333 --> 01:14:35,360
most people are perfectly content
living in their dreary little worlds.

968
01:14:36,539 --> 01:14:38,734
They just cling to the edge of the toilet bowl...

969
01:14:39,742 --> 01:14:41,471
trying to keep their heads above water...

970
01:14:41,544 --> 01:14:44,035
hoping some fool
won't come along, pull the chain.

971
01:14:45,514 --> 01:14:49,575
It's only when they hear that flushing sound
and they begin to slide down into the abyss...

972
01:14:49,652 --> 01:14:52,018
that they start taking stock of their lives.

973
01:14:57,960 --> 01:15:01,054
What about the people
who are so comfortable in their suffering...

974
01:15:01,130 --> 01:15:03,598
they don't even know
that the chain's been pulled?

975
01:15:09,238 --> 01:15:11,103
I know that you wanna write, Weldon.

976
01:15:11,540 --> 01:15:14,600
Oh, you just can't leave it alone, can you?

977
01:15:15,311 --> 01:15:17,643
No. No, I can't.

978
01:15:18,047 --> 01:15:19,412
But tell me I'm wrong.

979
01:15:20,082 --> 01:15:24,246
Weldon, look me in the eye
and tell me that you don't wanna write.

980
01:15:24,320 --> 01:15:27,221
- I don't wanna write.
- You know what I think?

981
01:15:27,590 --> 01:15:29,922
- I think that you miss it.
- No!

982
01:15:29,992 --> 01:15:32,187
I think that all the drinking
and all the craziness...

983
01:15:32,261 --> 01:15:34,991
is just your way of covering up
what's missing in your life.

984
01:15:35,064 --> 01:15:38,090
- Right.
- And everybody knows it, Weldon. Everybody.

985
01:15:38,167 --> 01:15:40,226
Your daughters know it,
Father Moretti knows it...

986
01:15:40,302 --> 01:15:41,633
Gustavo knows it, I know it.

987
01:15:41,704 --> 01:15:43,695
But what's worse is you know it.

988
01:15:43,772 --> 01:15:47,037
Tell me, hotshot,
you think knowing me a couple of weeks...

989
01:15:47,109 --> 01:15:49,543
and living 25 years of a sheltered existence...

990
01:15:49,612 --> 01:15:51,637
gives you the right
to tell me how to live my life?

991
01:15:51,714 --> 01:15:55,047
25 years or 25 minutes,
the truth is still the truth.

992
01:15:55,117 --> 01:15:57,108
My life is fine the way it is!

993
01:15:57,987 --> 01:15:59,818
I do what I want when I want!

994
01:16:00,189 --> 01:16:02,953
I pick a few grapes once a year.
That's all I have to do!

995
01:16:03,025 --> 01:16:05,289
I was just a writer, for God's sake!

996
01:16:06,695 --> 01:16:08,128
That's all I was!

997
01:16:09,031 --> 01:16:11,693
I didn't cure cancer, I didn't walk on the moon!

998
01:16:14,036 --> 01:16:15,526
The world isn't gonna stop spinning...

999
01:16:15,604 --> 01:16:18,334
- lf there isn't another Weldon Parish novel.
- You're right, it won't...

1000
01:16:18,407 --> 01:16:20,500
but maybe yours will start again.

1001
01:16:20,843 --> 01:16:22,640
And you are a writer, Weldon.

1002
01:16:22,711 --> 01:16:25,236
It is what you are
and you're a great one, at that.

1003
01:16:28,317 --> 01:16:32,253
A great writer knows
when he is not a great writer anymore.

1004
01:16:33,422 --> 01:16:37,449
- So then what, he just gives up?
- I didn't give anything up.

1005
01:16:38,560 --> 01:16:40,460
20 years ago I lost something.

1006
01:16:42,998 --> 01:16:45,125
Something more important than my writing.

1007
01:16:46,568 --> 01:16:49,833
How can I explain it to you?
I can't explain it to myself.

1008
01:16:49,905 --> 01:16:52,772
- Stop it. Just stop.
- Stop what?

1009
01:16:52,975 --> 01:16:57,708
If you don't wanna write, that's fine,
but stop blaming it on your dead wife.

1010
01:17:00,082 --> 01:17:01,071
[Groaning]

1011
01:17:07,289 --> 01:17:08,483
[Grunting]

1012
01:17:20,235 --> 01:17:21,429
[Panting]

1013
01:17:24,840 --> 01:17:26,535
[Crying] What do you want from me?

1014
01:17:27,443 --> 01:17:29,308
You want to prove I'm miserable?

1015
01:17:30,045 --> 01:17:32,570
You know, you say
you don't wanna write, Weldon...

1016
01:17:32,681 --> 01:17:34,740
but you write every single day.

1017
01:17:35,117 --> 01:17:37,278
You just stopped putting the pen to the page.

1018
01:17:37,753 --> 01:17:40,153
Sometimes life tosses you this way, that way...

1019
01:17:41,623 --> 01:17:44,717
and you find yourself in a place you never...

1020
01:17:45,728 --> 01:17:47,320
imagined you'd be in.

1021
01:17:48,664 --> 01:17:52,691
Before you realize it, it's too late to go back.

1022
01:17:53,001 --> 01:17:55,799
- No, it's never too late.
- I can't do it.

1023
01:17:55,871 --> 01:17:57,429
I don't believe you, Weldon.

1024
01:17:57,773 --> 01:17:59,240
- I can't.
- Why?

1025
01:17:59,541 --> 01:18:01,031
- Because...
- Because why?

1026
01:18:01,110 --> 01:18:02,702
Because I'm afraid!

1027
01:18:09,051 --> 01:18:11,019
Weldon, you're not afraid of writing.

1028
01:18:12,855 --> 01:18:14,288
You're afraid of failing.

1029
01:18:15,424 --> 01:18:16,857
We all fail.

1030
01:18:20,095 --> 01:18:21,653
Courage is in the trying.

1031
01:18:37,813 --> 01:18:39,337
[Sheep bleating]

1032
01:18:47,823 --> 01:18:49,290
[Birds chirping]

1033
01:18:54,496 --> 01:18:56,020
[People chattering]

1034
01:18:58,167 --> 01:18:59,191
[Jeremy sighing]

1035
01:18:59,268 --> 01:19:00,428
Are you all right?

1036
01:19:04,907 --> 01:19:08,900
You should've seen me today, Father.
You'd have been proud. I was very clever.

1037
01:19:10,779 --> 01:19:11,973
What happened?

1038
01:19:15,984 --> 01:19:18,578
I forced Weldon down a road
he didn't wanna go...

1039
01:19:20,222 --> 01:19:23,055
and I'm a little afraid
of what he's gonna find at the end of it.

1040
01:19:26,762 --> 01:19:31,358
Sometimes you must knock something down
in order to build something new.

1041
01:19:34,336 --> 01:19:39,000
Did it ever occur to you
that maybe the great Weldon Parish...

1042
01:19:39,074 --> 01:19:41,565
just simply does not have anything left to say?

1043
01:19:43,579 --> 01:19:45,547
You don't really believe that, do you?

1044
01:19:48,917 --> 01:19:49,906
[Sighing]

1045
01:19:49,985 --> 01:19:52,920
I know that you think
I'm his salvation, but I'm not.

1046
01:19:52,988 --> 01:19:54,853
I am just not.

1047
01:19:55,324 --> 01:19:58,293
Every night, I go home,
and I struggle to write...

1048
01:19:58,393 --> 01:20:01,453
one paragraph that tells me
that I have something...

1049
01:20:01,530 --> 01:20:04,055
anything important to say.

1050
01:20:04,132 --> 01:20:06,498
And there is a man
who can do it standing on his head...

1051
01:20:06,568 --> 01:20:08,866
and he chooses not to, he chooses that.

1052
01:20:08,937 --> 01:20:11,997
And I'm supposed to feel sorry for him?
Well, I'm sorry, I don't.

1053
01:20:12,074 --> 01:20:15,475
And I know life has dumped on him,
but life dumps on all of us, Father.

1054
01:20:15,544 --> 01:20:18,342
And we move on, we get past it.
At least most of us do.

1055
01:20:22,651 --> 01:20:25,415
Look, I'm not responsible for Weldon Parish.

1056
01:20:27,089 --> 01:20:28,750
I only did what I was sent here to do...

1057
01:20:28,824 --> 01:20:30,815
and I told him that
right from the very beginning.

1058
01:20:30,893 --> 01:20:32,451
It's not like I lied to him.

1059
01:20:33,862 --> 01:20:36,228
If that's true, why are you so upset?

1060
01:20:42,037 --> 01:20:44,471
[Speaking Italian]

1061
01:21:20,876 --> 01:21:22,935
[Chattering on TV]

1062
01:21:31,920 --> 01:21:34,946
Maura, where is everybody?

1063
01:21:37,326 --> 01:21:38,520
Still sleeping.

1064
01:21:38,727 --> 01:21:41,628
[Typewriter clacking]

1065
01:22:08,023 --> 01:22:10,355
[Door opening]

1066
01:23:13,789 --> 01:23:15,484
[Typewriter stops clacking]

1067
01:23:34,142 --> 01:23:35,700
[Exhaling]

1068
01:23:41,283 --> 01:23:42,875
What are you all gawking at?

1069
01:23:44,486 --> 01:23:46,477
You act as if
you've never seen a writer before.

1070
01:23:46,555 --> 01:23:49,115
[Girls laughing]

1071
01:24:00,368 --> 01:24:02,495
[All cheering]

1072
01:24:22,023 --> 01:24:23,354
You could stay.

1073
01:24:25,794 --> 01:24:27,227
And do what?

1074
01:24:29,264 --> 01:24:30,458
Write.

1075
01:24:33,835 --> 01:24:37,134
Besides, I don't think
I'd be the only one sad to see you go.

1076
01:24:40,208 --> 01:24:41,607
I don't know about that.

1077
01:24:44,646 --> 01:24:48,047
Jeremy, what have you got to go back to?

1078
01:24:50,552 --> 01:24:52,816
My life, my job.

1079
01:24:58,693 --> 01:25:01,389
I can't just pull up stakes
and move out here, Weldon.

1080
01:25:01,830 --> 01:25:03,058
Why not?

1081
01:25:05,033 --> 01:25:06,261
I have...

1082
01:25:10,071 --> 01:25:11,504
I just can't.

1083
01:25:14,509 --> 01:25:15,737
Well...

1084
01:25:18,980 --> 01:25:20,447
What about the contracts?

1085
01:25:22,384 --> 01:25:26,343
- What about them?
- Can't sign if you don't give them to me.

1086
01:25:34,963 --> 01:25:35,987
[Exhaling]

1087
01:25:36,064 --> 01:25:37,122
You know...

1088
01:25:39,267 --> 01:25:41,064
Why don't you just see how it goes?

1089
01:25:49,578 --> 01:25:51,671
I want you to write the book for yourself.

1090
01:25:53,515 --> 01:25:57,178
There's no need for you to have to deal
with the pressures of editors and publishers.

1091
01:25:58,520 --> 01:26:00,545
And if you like what you've written...

1092
01:26:01,623 --> 01:26:04,888
then, believe me,
we would be happy to publish it.

1093
01:26:10,799 --> 01:26:12,232
[Brakes squealing]

1094
01:26:20,375 --> 01:26:22,138
[Laughing]

1095
01:26:29,918 --> 01:26:31,943
- Arrivederci.
- Arrivederci.

1096
01:26:33,455 --> 01:26:34,444
JEREMY: Bye.

1097
01:26:34,522 --> 01:26:35,955
- Ciao, Jeremy.
- Ciao.

1098
01:26:37,158 --> 01:26:38,523
Goodbye, my son.

1099
01:26:39,694 --> 01:26:41,025
Ciao, Jeremy.

1100
01:26:44,599 --> 01:26:45,793
Isabella?

1101
01:26:48,570 --> 01:26:53,269
In Italy, we say a good friend is someone
who is there through the good and the bad.

1102
01:26:55,477 --> 01:26:57,445
[Speaking in Italian]

1103
01:26:58,113 --> 01:26:59,603
- Sir.
- Yeah?

1104
01:27:03,318 --> 01:27:05,946
And it's because
I can't imagine doing anything else.

1105
01:27:06,922 --> 01:27:10,915
- What?
- That's why I wanna be a writer.

1106
01:27:11,526 --> 01:27:13,858
Because I can't imagine doing anything else.

1107
01:27:20,335 --> 01:27:21,461
Okay.

1108
01:27:40,989 --> 01:27:42,650
- Bye, everybody.
- Ciao.

1109
01:27:42,724 --> 01:27:43,952
Ciao, Jeremy.

1110
01:27:50,532 --> 01:27:51,897
[Train whistle blowing]

1111
01:28:09,684 --> 01:28:11,049
[People chattering]

1112
01:28:29,037 --> 01:28:31,369
[Speaking Italian]

1113
01:28:36,111 --> 01:28:37,339
[Bird chirping]

1114
01:28:43,518 --> 01:28:45,110
[Speaking Italian]

1115
01:28:45,186 --> 01:28:47,586
I don't know... He broke his wing?

1116
01:28:48,423 --> 01:28:51,358
No fly. No fly.

1117
01:28:52,260 --> 01:28:54,524
Ah, no fly, no fly.

1118
01:28:56,965 --> 01:28:58,193
No fly.

1119
01:29:23,058 --> 01:29:24,218
[Speaking Italian]

1120
01:29:26,461 --> 01:29:27,826
[Brakes screeching]

1121
01:30:14,576 --> 01:30:15,804
Si, mama.

1122
01:30:26,988 --> 01:30:29,718
[Lo Che Amo Solo Te playing]

1123
01:31:58,988 --> 01:32:01,718
5@y3

